name: Georges Seurat | Hypernetwork
description:
Georges Seurat was a French post-impressionist artist who was famous for pioneering the distinctive painting technique known as pointillism. His most famous work, A Sunday Afternoon on the Island of La Grande Jatte, featuring many people sitting and enjoying a day at the park, is found at the Art Institute of Chicago.

This model is particularly well-suited for Seurat's favorite subjects of boats, beaches, seasides, sailing, and so on, and it handles people pretty well too.

This is a 1-1.5-1.5-1 Hypernetwork trained on SD v1.5-pruned-emaonly.ckpt.

modelVersions.name: v1
modelVersions.description:
This is a 1-1.5-1.5-1 Hypernetwork trained on SD v1.5-pruned-emaonly.ckpt.

This was trained in two stages, first with a 1e-4 rate for 800 steps, and then with a 5e-6 rate to 14,000 steps.
